    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>HDInsight<ph id=\"ph2\">](./media/fundamentals-introduction-to-azure/HDInsightIntroNew.png) </ph>",
      "pos": [
        57453,
        57532
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\"> **</bpt>Figure: HDInsight helps with the bulk processing of huge amounts of data<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        57535,
        57612
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For many years, the bulk of data analysis has been done on relational data stored in a data warehouse built with a relational DBMS.",
      "pos": [
        57614,
        57745
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This kind of business analytics is still important, and it will be for a long time to come.",
      "pos": [
        57746,
        57837
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "But what if the data you want to analyze is so big that relational databases just can't handle it?",
      "pos": [
        57838,
        57936
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "And suppose the data isn't relational?",
      "pos": [
        57937,
        57975
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It might be server logs in a datacenter, for example, or historical event data from sensors, or something else.",
      "pos": [
        57976,
        58087
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In cases like this, you have what's known as a big data problem.",
      "pos": [
        58088,
        58152
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You need another approach.",
      "pos": [
        58153,
        58179
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The dominant technology today for analyzing big data is Hadoop.",
      "pos": [
        58181,
        58244
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An Apache open source project, this technology stores data using the Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS), then lets developers create MapReduce jobs to analyze that data.",
      "pos": [
        58245,
        58417
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "HDFS spreads data across multiple servers, then runs chunks of the MapReduce job on each one, letting the big data be processed in parallel.",
      "pos": [
        58418,
        58558
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "HDInsight is the name of the Azure's Apache Hadoop-based service.",
      "pos": [
        58560,
        58625
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "HDInsight lets HDFS store data on the cluster and distribute it across multiple VMs.",
      "pos": [
        58626,
        58710
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It also spreads the logic of a MapReduce job across those VMs.",
      "pos": [
        58711,
        58773
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Just as with on-premises Hadoop, data is processed locally-the logic and the data it works on are in the same VM-and in parallel for better performance.",
      "pos": [
        58774,
        58926
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "HDInsight can also store data in Azure Storage Vault (ASV), which uses blobs.",
      "pos": [
        58927,
        59004
      ]
